Summer Sunday Skincare Routine using @emmalewisham 
After apply layers of sunscreen all day at the beach, your pores can become clogged causing uneven skin tone and breakouts.

I'll show you the best way to exfoliate and keep your skin ultra clean and glowing.

Here are 3 steps to get your skin back to looking great.

Step 1. Use @emmalewisham Illuminating Face Exfoliant. Great to gently remove sunscreen, makeup build up and to help rejuvenate the skin.

Step 2. Lather on @emmalewisham Supernatural Sleeping Mask. This mask 
Boosts Collagen, Nourishes Skin and Hydrates so effectively. 
I love to lather it on for 5-10mims then wipe the excess off and massage into the skin. I wake up with the most plumped and nourished skin. It stimulates cell turnover and repairs skin barrier while you sleep.

Step 3. When I wake up I use Supernatural Face Oil to give me that extra glow before apply my makeup.
This oil is so good. The oils contain Vitamin A & E which visibly improves the appearance of fine lines and wrinkles, smooths and tones the complexion.

I've recommended Supernatural Face Oil to my friends and I've seen their skin transform. Their skin texture has changed dramatically. Skin is hydrated, smoothed and I can see their skin start to have this beautiful glaze. 
I think the Supernatural Face Oil is my favorite product out of the #EmmaLewisham #Skincare line.

This weeks shoots. Using @emmalewisham
The most important part of my set day is in the morning. If the models skin isn't perfected with the correct skincare, it can totally mess up the day and the images.
That's why it's so important for me to use the highest quality skincare products on my models and clients.

My clients book me because they know they will get flawless and naturally glowing skin. To achieve this instantly,
I love using @emmalewisham Supernatural Face Oil. The face oil gives that extra radiance before apply makeup.  As soon as I apply the oil, you can see the skin glisten.
Perfect for all skin types.

#EmmaLewisham Supernatural sleeping mask is another great on set product. Leave the mask on for 5-10mins, wipe off excess product and massage the rest into the skin.
Skin will be completely hydrated, smooth and illuminated.
The best preparation for a long days shoot. Foundation and concealers will melt over the top. Trust me. I use it everyday.
These steps make ALL the difference before apply any makeup product. #intelligentskincare
